%N A397870 Decimal expansion of the midradius of a canonical (dual-uniform) heptagonal trapezohedron with unit short edge length.
%C A397870 The heptagonal trapezohedron is the dual polyhedron of the heptagonal antiprism.
%H A397870 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A397870/b397870.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A397870 David I. McCooey, <a href="https://dmccooey.com/polyhedra/HeptagonalTrapezohedron.html">Heptagonal Trapezohedron</a>.
%H A397870 Polytope Wiki, <a href="https://polytope.miraheze.org/wiki/Heptagonal_antitegum">Heptagonal antitegum</a>.
%H A397870 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Trapezohedron.html">Trapezohedron</a>.
%H A397870 <a href="/index/Al#algebraic_06">Index entries for algebraic numbers, degree 6</a>.
%F A397870 Equals csc(Pi/14)*sqrt(1 + 2*cos(Pi/7))/4 = csc(Pi/14)*sqrt(1 + A160389)/4.
%F A397870 Equals the largest real root of 64*x^6 - 240*x^4 + 48*x^2 + 1.
%e A397870 1.8806084134241580556945404745078513039819230528350...
%t A397870 First[RealDigits[Csc[Pi/14]*Sqrt[1 + 2*Cos[Pi/7]]/4, 10, 100]]
%t A397870 (* Alternative: *)
%t A397870 First[RealDigits[PolyhedronData[{"Trapezohedron", 7}, "Midradius"], 10, 100]]
%Y A397870 Cf. A397867 (volume), A397868 (surface area), A397869 (inradius), A397871 (height).
%Y A397870 Cf. A397872 (long edge).
%Y A397870 Cf. A397873 (small face angle), A397874 (large face angle), A397875 (dihedral angle).
%Y A397870 Cf. A394073 (midradius of the dual).
%Y A397870 Cf. A160389.
